WHAT IS THIS?
==============================================================================

This license governs how other people can use, modify, and share this
software. Read it before using MIDI2Psych in your own projects.

Some terms used below explained in plain English:

  Personal use
      You're using it for yourself -- hobby projects, research, learning,
      tinkering. No money changes hands and it's not part of a business.

  Commercial use
      Anything where money is involved or the software contributes to a
      product or service that generates revenue. This includes using it
      internally at a company, bundling it in a paid product, offering it
      as part of a service, or saving your business time/money with it.
      If in doubt, it counts as commercial.

  Modify
      Changing the source code -- fixing bugs, adding features, porting it
      to another platform, or building something new on top of it.

  Redistribute
      Sharing the software with other people, whether that's uploading it
      somewhere, including it in another project, or passing it along.

  Open source / Closed source
      Open source means the source code is publicly available. Closed source
      (also called proprietary) means the source code is kept private. If
      you modify this software and share it, you must keep it open source.

  Fork
      A copy of this project that you've taken and developed independently.
      Forks must follow the same rules as the original.

==============================================================================
WHAT YOU CAN DO
==============================================================================

  [YES] Use it for personal, non-commercial purposes
        You can use MIDI2Psych freely for hobby projects, personal research,
        education, or anything else that isn't commercial.

  [YES] Modify it
        You can change the source code however you like for personal use.
        Go wild.

  [YES] Redistribute it
        You can share this software or modified versions of it, as long as
        you follow the conditions in the next section.

==============================================================================
WHAT YOU CANNOT DO
==============================================================================

  [NO]  Use it commercially
        You may not use this software -- or any modified version of it --
        in a commercial context. This includes but is not limited to:
          - Products or services that generate revenue
          - Internal business tooling at a company
          - Freelance or contract work
          - SaaS platforms, apps, or tools offered to paying customers
        If you want a commercial license, get in touch.

  [NO]  Distribute closed-source forks
        If you modify this software and share it with anyone, the full
        source code of your modified version must also be made publicly
        available under this same license. You cannot keep your changes
        private while distributing the compiled result.

  [NO]  Use the author's name to promote your work
        You may not use the name "Ollie Quayle" or "MIDI2Psych" to endorse,
        advertise, or promote any software derived from this project without
        explicit written permission.

